			<h2 class="excerpt">本来说互联网会给我们的大脑提供很多知识，但我们又学到了些什么呢？其实我们的大脑需要的可不只是知识</h2>
		<div class="detail">
					<!-- 普通文章 -->
					<p class="">
</p>
<p>
	<span><span><strong><a href="http://aeon.co/users/dougald-hine">Dougald Hine</a>&nbsp;</strong></span><strong>是一位英国作家。他创立了万物学院（</strong></span><span><strong>School of Everything</strong></span><span><strong>）、</strong></span><span><strong>Spacemakers</strong></span><span><strong> 和崩溃学学会（</strong></span><span><strong>Institute for Collapsonomics</strong></span><span><strong>）。他还和保罗</strong></span><span><strong>·</strong></span><span><strong>金斯诺斯（</strong></span><span><strong>Paul Kingsnorth</strong></span><span><strong>）合著有《远离文明：黑暗之山的宣言》（</strong></span><span><i><strong>Uncivilisation: The Dark Mountain Manifesto</strong></i></span><span><strong>）一书。</strong></span> 
</p><p class="medium-insert-active"><strong><a href="http://aeon.co/essays/how-can-we-be-bored-when-we-have-google" target="_blank">本文</a></strong><strong>由 </strong><strong><a href="http://aeon.co/" target="_blank">AEON</a> </strong><strong>授权《好奇心日报》发布，你可以在 Twitter 上关注<a href="http://twitter.com/aeonmag" target="_blank">他们</a>。</strong><span><strong><br></strong></span></p>
<p>
</p>
